declare_parcel_as_script_with_stdin <<'/---'
Handle core standard error functionality. See @{stdin} for further details.
/---

# ....................{ TESTERS                            }....................
declare_function_with_stdin <<'/---'
[status: bool] is_stderr_terminal()

Report success if standard error from the current context is a terminal.
/---
function is_stderr_terminal() {
    die_if_args
    is -t ${ZESHY_STDERR_FILE_DESCRIPTOR-2} si
}

# --------------------( WASTELANDS                         )--------------------
